<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-25T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="329" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">123M956/386: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers (<persName type="from">Cole</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-26T00:00:00+01:00">July
                                        26, 1942—midnight.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received July 27—10:41 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>490. From Murphy. Your 220, July 24, 9 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>] I do not foresee any difficulty returning to North
                                Africa. I hold visas for the three French North African territories
                                good until February 1943 and no visa is required for the Tangier
                                Zone. [Murphy.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>